<!--
VOICING PLAN:
- Pickup + Phrase 1 (mm. 0-4): C#m open entry. Alternates C#m and E, pivoting through A(IV).
  LH uses full open voicings: C#2-G#2-C#3-E3 for vi, E2-B2-E3-G#3 for I.
- Phrase 2 (mm. 5-8): Bridge. G#m(iii) as substitute for Ebm (enharmonic D#m).
  F#m-E-F#m rapid sequence bar 6, then C#m compression in bar 7.
- Phrase 3 (mm. 9-12): Fuller return. B(V) with D#4 tritone color (bar 9). Stepwise
  chord descent A→G#m→F#m (bar 10). Asus2 suspension (bar 12).
- Phrase 4 (mm. 13-15): Final cadence. ii(F#m)→vi(C#m) plagal-like resolution.
  Bar 15 closes on C#m — the piece is in the aeolian mode on C#, Lydian on E.

VOICE LEADING HIGHLIGHTS:
- Bar 2: A→G#m, RH C#5-E5→B4-D#5 (step+step down), LH A3-C#4→B3-D#3 (step up).
- Bar 6: Three chords per bar (F#m-E-F#m) — LH returns to same voicing, smooth.
- Bar 10: Stepwise LH descent: A2-E3-A3 → G#2-D#3-G#3 → F#2-C#3-F#3.
- Bar 14: C#5 common tone held in RH through F#m→C#m change.

TEXTURE ARC:
- Pickup: single note entry, C#m
- mm. 1-4: Light 2-note RH, 4-note LH. Modal E landscape.
- mm. 5-8: Bridge — G#m tension, rapid F#m changes, low C#m compression
- mm. 9-12: Return — B(V) high register, descending thirds, sus2 on A
- mm. 13-15: Final cadence — fullest chords, ii→vi closes in C# minor
-->
